FBIS3-4338 "drchi060_v_94005" FBIS-CHI-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 TAIWAN Kuomintang Head in Tokyo on President's Attending APEC OW2503135594 Taipei CNA in English 1331 GMT 25 Mar 94 OW2503135594 Taipei CNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [By Victor Lai] [Text] Tokyo, March 25 (CNA) -- Kuomintang Secretary-General Hsu Shui-the on Thursday [24 March] asked several Japanese political leaders to help create an environment that will enable President Li Teng-hui to attend the Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation [APEC] forum leadership conference in November in Indonesia. Hsu expressed the wish when he called on Yoshiro Mori, the secretary-general of the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP]; Keizo Obuchi, a former LDP secretary-general, and Takeo Fukuda, a former prime minister. He said that if Li could attend the Indonesian APEC meeting, then there would be no big obstacles in the way of his attending the 1995 APEC leadership conference in Japan.
